  - question: How much does a product landing page cost?
    answer: >-
      A custom product landing page typically costs between $1,500 and $5,000 depending on the design complexity, animations, and number of sections. This is significantly less than hiring an agency, which can charge $10,000 or more for similar work.
  - question: How long does it take to build a landing page?
    answer: >-
      A single product landing page usually takes 1 to 2 weeks from design to launch. This includes the initial design, development, responsive testing across devices, and one round of revisions. Simpler pages can be done in under a week.
  - question: Why use a dark theme for a product landing page?
    answer: >-
      Dark themes make physical products stand out visually. Hardware, electronics, and premium products pop against dark backgrounds because the contrast draws attention to the product images. It also creates a modern, tech-forward impression instantly.
  - question: What makes a good product landing page?
    answer: >-
      A good product landing page puts the product front and center with large, sharp images and minimal distractions. It needs scannable feature sections, smooth scroll animations, fast load times, and a mobile-first design since most visitors browse on their phones.
  - question: Can a freelancer build a landing page as good as an agency?
    answer: >-
      Yes. A skilled freelance developer can deliver the same quality as an agency for a fraction of the cost. The difference is you work directly with the person building your page, which means faster communication, fewer layers, and quicker turnaround.
  - question: Why does page speed matter for product landing pages?
    answer: >-
      Most visitors tap on 2-3 search results when comparing products. If your page takes more than 3 seconds to load, they move on to a competitor. A fast-loading page built with a framework like Astro ships almost zero JavaScript, keeping load times under 1 second.
