## Can a startup landing page compete with major brands?

I built Doorly a product landing page that looks as polished as Ring or Nest for a fraction of what an agency would charge. The dark-themed, animation-rich page was delivered in one week and loads in under a second on any device.

Doorly makes smart doorbells and they were competing against brands like Ring and Nest. They needed a product landing page that looked just as polished as the big players, but they didn't have the budget for an agency. That's where I came in.

## Why did I choose a dark UI for this product?

The dark UI was a no-brainer for this one. Hardware products pop on dark backgrounds, and it gives the page that modern tech feel instantly.

The hero section puts the product front and center with a big, sharp image and clean text. No sidebars, no popups, nothing fighting for attention. As you scroll down, each feature section fades in using GSAP ScrollTrigger. I kept the animations smooth and subtle because the goal is to feel polished, not distracting. Each feature gets a short headline, an icon, and two lines of text. People browsing for a doorbell want quick, scannable info.

## How did I handle responsive product images?

One thing I spent extra time on was making the product images responsive. A hero image that looks perfect at 1440px wide can break completely on a phone screen if you don't set up the scaling properly. On this project, mobile was the priority since most of their traffic comes from phones.

The whole site is static HTML through Astro, so page speed is excellent. No React, no heavy framework loading in the browser. Just fast, clean pages.

## What was the result?

Built the full page in about a week, including one round of tweaks on animation speed. The client was really happy with how it looked on mobile, and the page loads fast enough that they're not losing visitors to slow speeds.
